Wasps, Perpignan, Leicester and
Biarritz had home wins in European rugbyâ€™s Heineken Cup today.  Joe Simpson, Tom Varndell, Ben Jacobs and Dominic Waldouck
scored tries for Wasps in a 38-26 win over Glasgow. Perpignan
beat Treviso 35-14, Leicester won 46-10 over Scarlets, and
Ulster went down 35-15 at Biarritz.  Biarritz leads Pool 4, three points ahead of Bath, which
downed Aironi 22-6 yesterday. Leicester has a four-point lead
over Perpignan in Pool 5, and Wasps are two points behind the
Pool 6 leader, defending champion Toulouse.  Previously this weekend, Toulouse, Munster and Northampton
all won, and there were also victories for Ospreys, Castres,
Leinster and Racing Metro.  Northampton leads Pool 1 by three points over Castres,
Leinster has a four-point advantage over Clermont Auvergne in
Pool 2, and Munster tops Pool 3 by a point from Ospreys.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
